    public class DFSSampler
extends java.lang.Object
implements Sampler
    Class is for a sampler that sorts the maximum likelihood matches and sorts them. We may have a lot of mismatches so this sampler will choose over a distribution of the most likely ones to return
    Author:
    Aptima

      • DFSSampler

        public DFSSampler(int maxSamplesToGenerate,
          int dataNodeCount,
          MismatchValues mismatches,
          BPMathModelNode[] modelNodes,
          BPMathModelRelation[] modelRelations,
          java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.String> DataNodeToID,
          double probDecrFactor,
          int maxBranchingFactor,
          int maxTopLevelIterations,
          int maxRecLevelIterations,
          double sliderValue)
        Constructor Samples the results after BP. After BP runs, we have notional probabilities for individual matches. Sampler strings those all together and produces a sample/match. Match the first model node to a data node, and then the next likely one. Back thing out if it goes down to a hole. Also equivalent matches are taken into account because things could be symmetric.
        Parameters:
        maxSamplesToGenerate - limit samples and max recursionDepth
        dataNodeCount - number of data nodes
        mismatches - the node and relation mismatches
        modelNodes - the model nodes
        modelRelations - the model relations
        DataNodeToID - ID is integer of data node and String is the name of the data node
        probDecrFactor - TODO: Check: Seems like it is set with the slider as part of the threshold
        maxBranchingFactor - Follow at most maxBranchingFactor links at each level of recursion
        maxTopLevelIterations - Consider at most maxTopLevelIterations nodes at the top level
        maxRecLevelIterations - Consider at most maxRecLevelIterations nodes at each subsequent level // (only the ones with compatible link information turn into branches
        sliderValue - Sets threshold from a slider
